Trần Lê Yên Nhiên is an Intern/Fresher Network Engineer/Specialist with no commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in foundational networking concepts including Network Design, Network Configuration, and Network Security, complemented by an understanding of IoT principles. Academically, they have engaged in practical team activities, notably designing an IoT product for a course, demonstrating early application of IoT concepts. Currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Networks and Data Communications at Tôn Đức Thắng University, they are building a strong academic foundation in the field.
Technically, they are proficient in programming languages such as C, Python, and Java, and have hands-on experience with networking simulation and emulation tools including Cisco Packet Tracer and eve-ng. Further enhancing their profile, Trần Lê Yên Nhiên holds an Aptis ESOL certification, an Ethical Hacker Course Completion Certificate (expected 2025), and a Microsoft Office Specialist (MOS) certification (expected 2025), showcasing a commitment to professional development and a solid academic performance with a GPA of 7.0.